<h2 class="bac">Summary:</h2>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Strong A&ndash;level grades and on track for a minimum 2:1 degree (or equivalent)</li>
	<li>Primary locations: London, Bromley & Chester (all in the UK)</li>
	<li>Desk&ndash;specific, 9&ndash;week programme from June – August</li>
	<li>Online application form</li>
	<li>Application Deadline: 17 December 2010</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Markets Operations/Middle Office Group (GMO&#38;MO) provides controlled and cost&ndash;effective post&ndash;trade processes in support of our Capital Markets, Corporate Investments, Corporate Treasury, Global Wealth and Investment Management businesses. 
</p>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Middle Office </H3>
<p class="bac">
This group within GMO&#38;MO delivers control functions responsible for providing assurance over data and processes used to record risk, P/L, balance sheet and financial results in support of Global Markets, Corporate Treasury and Corporate Investments businesses. There are seven core GMO functions that are critical in ensuring business process control: new business development, trade capture substantiation, P&#38;L validation, risk/position validation, balance sheet substantiation, event monitoring and front&ndash;back process oversight. 
</p>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Global Markets Operations</H3>
<p class="bac">
Some of the core processes in this group include confirmations, client services and on&ndash;boarding, trades processing, settlements and custody and asset servicing. With approximately 20 million transactions per day, the organisational infrastructure is designed to ensure global consistency of processes and strong global and local supervision.  
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
The Summer Intern Programme within GMO&#38;MO is a precursor to the full&ndash;time programme. As a Summer Analyst, you&#39;ll: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Be exposed to a broad range of teams and products, assigned to either the Operations or Middle Office division </li>
	<li>Take on roles that range from P&#38;L validation, trade control or balance sheet substantiation to clearing, settlements, or work with operational risk</li>
	<li>Enjoy a rich and varied working experience</li>
	<li>Work closely with colleagues throughout our organisation to build relationships</li>
	<li>Gain the knowledge and expertise to meet the challenges critical to this function</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Strong academic qualifications are important, but you&#39;ll also need to demonstrate drive, innovation and a dedication to a career in Middle Office or Global Operations. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
We accept applications from a diverse range of degree disciplines, although maths, accounting and finance subjects are key for this line of business. In addition, teamwork, leadership, problem&ndash;solving skills and creativity are important, as is the ability to work in a fast&ndash;paced environment, multi&ndash;task and interact with a variety of people. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The best opportunity to learn about working life at the company is to experience it first&ndash;hand through our nine&ndash;week Summer Programme. Aimed at students in their penultimate year, the programme runs from June to the end of August, and is designed to help you decide whether our offering matches your aspirations.  
</p>
<p class="bac">
Working on real tasks, problems, issues or projects alongside our associates will provide you with a unique learning opportunity and exposure to life at a leading investment bank. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
The programme includes: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Classroom instruction prior to assignment</li>
	<li>Senior Speaker Series, featuring presentations by top executives </li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior managers and network with peers </li>
	<li>A mentoring programme</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
If you perform well during your time, you may go back to university with a job offer for the following year, enabling you to truly focus on your studies. 
</p>

